00:15:37,118 --> 00:15:39,177
but when l took over
this department...

237
00:15:39,253 --> 00:15:41,847
it had the worst programming record
in television history.

238
00:15:41,923 --> 00:15:44,721
This network hasn't one show
in the top 20.

239
00:15:44,792 --> 00:15:46,851
This network is an industry joke.

240
00:15:46,928 --> 00:15:50,227
We better start putting together
one winner for next September.

241
00:15:50,298 --> 00:15:52,232
l want a show developed...

242
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,895
based on the activities
of a terrorist group.

243
00:15:55,970 --> 00:15:58,370
"Joseph Stalin and His Merry Band
of Bolsheviks."

244
00:15:58,439 --> 00:16:01,806
l want ideas from you.
That is what you're paid for.

245
00:16:01,876 --> 00:16:05,642
By the way, the next time l send
an audience research report around...

246
00:16:05,713 --> 00:16:08,147
you'd better read it,
or l'll sack the lot of you.

247
00:16:08,215 --> 00:16:09,842
ls that clear?

248
00:16:09,917 --> 00:16:15,583
l'll be on the coast in four weeks. Can
you set up a meeting with Laureen Hobbs?

249
00:16:15,656 --> 00:16:19,251
The business of management
is management.

250
00:16:19,327 --> 00:16:22,694
At the time CCA took control,
the UBS TV network was foundering...

251
00:16:22,763 --> 00:16:26,290
with less than seven percent
of national television revenues...

252
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:29,234
most network programs being sold
at station rates.

253
00:16:29,303 --> 00:16:32,898
l am pleased to announce l am submitting
to the board of directors a plan...

254
00:16:32,974 --> 00:16:35,704
for the coordination
of the main profit centers...

255
00:16:35,776 --> 00:16:38,745
and with the specific intention
of making each division...

256
00:16:38,813 --> 00:16:41,611
more responsive to management.

257
00:16:41,682 --> 00:16:43,115
Point one.

258
00:16:44,518 --> 00:16:48,010
"The division producing the lowest rate
of return has been the News Division...

259
00:16:48,089 --> 00:16:53,652
with its $98 million budget and its
average annual deficit of $32 million."

260
00:16:54,829 --> 00:16:58,162
l know, historically, news divisions
are expected to lose money.

261
00:16:58,232 --> 00:17:01,065
To our minds, this philosophy
is a wanton fiscal affront...

262
00:17:01,135 --> 00:17:04,832
to be resolutely resisted.

263
00:17:04,905 --> 00:17:10,366
The new plan calls for local news to be
transferred to Owned Stations Divisions.

264
00:17:10,444 --> 00:17:13,971
News Radio would be transferred to
the UBS Radio Division...

265
00:17:14,048 --> 00:17:18,109
and the News Division would be reduced
from an independent division...

266
00:17:18,185 --> 00:17:22,713
to a department accountable
to network.

267
00:17:27,628 --> 00:17:31,086
- What was that all about, Ed?
- This is not the time.

268
00:17:31,165 --> 00:17:33,099
Why wasn't l told about this?

269
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:37,467
Why was l led up onto that podium and
humiliated in front of the stockholders?

270
00:17:37,538 --> 00:17:39,972
Goddamn it! l spoke to John Wheeler
this morning...

271
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:42,669
and he assured me
that the News Division was safe.

272
00:17:42,743 --> 00:17:44,973
lf you want me to resign,
that's a bad way to do it.

273
00:17:45,046 --> 00:17:47,947
We'll talk about this tomorrow
at our regular morning meeting.

274
00:18:00,061 --> 00:18:02,029
Roll VTA.

275
00:18:02,096 --> 00:18:04,326
Bring it up on one.
Ready now.

276
00:18:05,199 --> 00:18:09,158
ln five, four, three, two--

277
00:18:09,236 --> 00:18:11,431
- One.
- One TVA.

278
00:18:12,873 --> 00:18:14,306
And...

279
00:18:16,143 --> 00:18:17,576
cue announcer.

280
00:18:17,645 --> 00:18:19,613
The " UBS Evening News" ...

281
00:18:20,815 --> 00:18:22,840
with Howard Beale.

282
00:18:22,917 --> 00:18:24,817
Ready two.

283
00:18:24,885 --> 00:18:26,409
Two. Cue power.

284
00:18:26,487 --> 00:18:30,514
Good evening.
Today is Wednesday, September 24...

285
00:18:30,591 --> 00:18:32,525
and this is my last broadcast.

286
00:18:33,961 --> 00:18:35,895
Yesterday l announced
on this program...

287
00:18:35,963 --> 00:18:38,932
that l was going to commit
public suicide...

288
00:18:38,999 --> 00:18:41,559
admittedly an act of madness.

289
00:18:41,635 --> 00:18:44,729
l'll tell you what happened.
l just ran out of bullshit.

290
00:18:44,805 --> 00:18:47,103
- Cut him off.
- Leave him on.

291
00:18:48,542 --> 00:18:49,975
Am l still on?

292
00:18:50,044 --> 00:18:53,138
lf this is how he wants to go out,
this is how he goes out.

293
00:18:53,214 --> 00:18:55,478
l just ran out of bullshit.

294
00:18:55,549 --> 00:18:58,017
Mr. Schumacher's here.
Do you want to talk to him?

295
00:18:58,085 --> 00:19:00,019
Bullshit is all the reasons
we give for living.

296
00:19:00,087 --> 00:19:04,387
lf we can't think up reasons of our own,
we always have the God bullshit.

297
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:06,323
- We don't know why we go through...
- What is it?

298
00:19:06,393 --> 00:19:08,861
pointless pain,
humiliation and decay.

299
00:19:08,929 --> 00:19:12,865
There better be someone, somewhere
who does know. That's the God bullshit.

300
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:16,369
He's saying that life is bullshit.
lt is. What are you screaming about?

301
00:19:16,437 --> 00:19:19,873
Man is a noble creature who can order
his own world. Who needs God?

302
00:19:21,075 --> 00:19:24,943
lf there's anybody who can look around
this demented world we live in...

303
00:19:25,012 --> 00:19:28,038
and tell me man
is a noble creature...

304
00:19:28,115 --> 00:19:30,413
believe me,
that man is full of bullshit.

305
00:19:31,519 --> 00:19:35,114
- What's so goddamn funny?
- l can't help it. lt's funny.

306
00:19:36,891 --> 00:19:39,860
This is going out live
to 67 affiliates.

307
00:19:39,927 --> 00:19:41,360
Leave him on.

308
00:19:41,428 --> 00:19:45,922
And l was married for 33 years
of shrill, shrieking fraud.

309
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,595
- Mr. Hackett's trying to reach you.
- Tell Mr. Hackett to go fuck himself.

310
00:19:49,670 --> 00:19:52,662
So l don't have any bullshit left.

311
00:19:53,808 --> 00:19:56,800
l just ran out of it, you see.

312
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:04,984
Mr. Ruddy, could we have
one statement, please?

313
00:20:05,052 --> 00:20:07,145
Sorry, l don't have
all the information yet.

314
00:20:10,624 --> 00:20:14,560
lf we could just have one statement
about Mr. Beale.

315
00:20:24,572 --> 00:20:26,005
Max?

316
00:20:34,815 --> 00:20:36,749
l'll want to see Mr. Beale
after this.

317
00:20:39,286 --> 00:20:41,880
The way l hear it,
you were primarily responsible...

318
00:20:41,956 --> 00:20:44,288
for this colossally
stupid prank.

319
00:20:45,025 --> 00:20:47,323
- ls that the fact?
- That's the fact.

320
00:20:47,394 --> 00:20:49,954
lt was unconscionable.

321
00:20:53,334 --> 00:20:56,770
- There is nothing more to say.
- l have something to say.

322
00:20:57,905 --> 00:21:00,772
l want to know why that debasement
of the News Division...

323
00:21:00,841 --> 00:21:04,470
announced at the meeting this afternoon
was kept secret from me?

324
00:21:05,713 --> 00:21:08,045
You and l go back 20 years.

325
00:21:08,115 --> 00:21:10,640
l took this job
with your personal assurance...

326
00:21:10,718 --> 00:21:14,484
that you'd back my autonomy
against any encroachment.

327
00:21:14,555 --> 00:21:19,288
But ever since CCA acquired control
of UBS Systems ten months ago...

328
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,692
Hackett's been taking over everything.

329
00:21:21,762 --> 00:21:25,960
Who is running this network?
You or some conglomerate called CCA?

330
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:28,831
You're president
of the Systems Group.

331
00:21:28,903 --> 00:21:32,464
Hackett's nothing
but a hatchet man for CCA.

332
00:21:32,539 --> 00:21:35,201
Nelson here,
president of the network...

333
00:21:35,276 --> 00:21:38,040
and he hasn't a damned thing to say
about anything anymore.

334
00:21:38,112 --> 00:21:40,706
l told you
at the stockholders' meeting...

335
00:21:40,781 --> 00:21:44,615
that we would discuss all that
at our regular meeting tomorrow morning.

336
00:21:44,685 --> 00:21:47,017
lf you had been patient,
l would have explained...

337
00:21:47,087 --> 00:21:49,647
that l, too, thought
Frank Hackett precipitate...

338
00:21:49,723 --> 00:21:52,624
and that the reorganization of the
News Division would not be executed...

339
00:21:52,693 --> 00:21:55,218
until everyone,
specifically you, Max...

340
00:21:55,296 --> 00:21:58,231
had been consulted and satisfied.

341
00:21:59,199 --> 00:22:01,133
lnstead, you sulked off
like a child...

342
00:22:01,201 --> 00:22:04,227
and engaged this network
in a shocking and disgraceful episode.

343
00:22:04,305 --> 00:22:06,296
Your position
is no longer tenable...

344
00:22:06,373 --> 00:22:08,705
regardless of how management
is restructured.

345
00:22:10,778 --> 00:22:13,008
l will expect your resignation
at 10:00 tomorrow morning.

346
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:16,811
We will coordinate our statements
to the least detriment of everyone.

347
00:22:18,953 --> 00:22:22,411
Bob McDonough will take over the News
Division until we sort all this out.

348
00:22:24,491 --> 00:22:27,289
l'd like to see Mr. Beale now.

349
00:22:27,361 --> 00:22:30,125
They're looking for him.
They don't know where he is.

350
00:22:31,465 --> 00:22:35,162
Well, every day, five days a week
for 15 years...

351
00:22:35,235 --> 00:22:38,762
l've been sitting behind that desk,
the dispassionate pundit...

352
00:22:38,839 --> 00:22:41,865
reporting with seemly detachment...

353
00:22:41,942 --> 00:22:45,537
the daily parade of lunacies
that constitute the news.

354
00:22:45,612 --> 00:22:47,045
Just once...

355
00:22:47,114 --> 00:22:49,105
l wanted to say
what l really felt.

356
00:22:49,183 --> 00:22:50,810
Knock it off.

357
00:22:50,884 --> 00:22:52,749
lt was, after all, my last one.

358
00:23:09,803 --> 00:23:12,465
- Have the overnight ratings come in?
- They're on your desk.

359
00:23:12,539 --> 00:23:14,473
Have you got
yesterday's overnights?

360
00:23:14,541 --> 00:23:16,771
- Shall l bring them in?
- Yeah.

361
00:23:22,483 --> 00:23:25,577
These are the outlines submitted
by Universal for an hour series.

362
00:23:25,652 --> 00:23:28,712
You needn't bother to read them.
l'll tell them to you.

363
00:23:28,789 --> 00:23:33,385
The first one is set in an eastern
law school, presumably Harvard.

364
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:36,588
The series is irresistibly entitled
"The New Lawyers."

365
00:23:36,663 --> 00:23:40,030
The running characters are: a crusty
but benign ex-Supreme Court justice...

366
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:43,536
presumably Oliver Wendell Holmes
by way of Dr. Zorba...

367
00:23:43,604 --> 00:23:47,040
a beautiful girl graduate student,
and the local district attorney...

368
00:23:47,107 --> 00:23:49,041
who is brilliant
and sometimes cuts corners.

369
00:23:49,109 --> 00:23:51,009
Next one.

370
00:23:51,078 --> 00:23:53,069
The second one's called
"The Amazon Squad."

371
00:23:53,147 --> 00:23:54,705
Lady cops.

372
00:23:54,782 --> 00:23:57,615
Running characters include a crusty
but benign police lieutenant...

373
00:23:57,684 --> 00:23:59,982
who's always getting heat
from the commissioner...

374
00:24:00,054 --> 00:24:03,785
a tough, hard-drinking detective who
thinks women belong in the kitchen...

375
00:24:03,857 --> 00:24:07,554
and a brilliant, beautiful young cop
who's fighting the feminist battle.

376
00:24:07,628 --> 00:24:09,687
We're up to our ears in lady cops.

377
00:24:09,763 --> 00:24:12,857
Next is another one of those
investigative reporter shows.

378
00:24:12,933 --> 00:24:15,561
A crusty but benign managing editor
who's always getting--

379
00:24:15,636 --> 00:24:17,729
You know, Barbara...

380
00:24:17,805 --> 00:24:22,105
the Arabs have decided to jack up
the price of oil another 20 percent.

381
00:24:23,077 --> 00:24:26,877
The ClA has been caught opening
Senator Humphrey's mail.

382
00:24:26,947 --> 00:24:30,906
There's a civil war in Angola.
Another one in Beirut.

383
00:24:32,186 --> 00:24:34,711
New York City's still facing default.

384
00:24:34,788 --> 00:24:37,655
They finally caught up
with Patricia Hearst.

385
00:24:37,724 --> 00:24:41,455
And the whole front page
of the Daily News is Howard Beale.

386
00:24:42,563 --> 00:24:46,522
There's also a two-column story
on page one of the Times.

387
00:24:49,336 --> 00:24:51,668
Helen?
Call Mr. Hackett's office.

388
00:24:51,738 --> 00:24:54,172
See if he can give me
a few minutes this morning.

389
00:25:00,781 --> 00:25:05,150
KTNS Kansas City refuses to carry
our " Network News Show" anymore...

390
00:25:05,219 --> 00:25:07,153
unless Beale is taken off the air.

391
00:25:07,221 --> 00:25:09,348
Did you see the overnights
on the " Network News" ?

392
00:25:09,423 --> 00:25:12,153
lt has an 8 in New York,
a 9 in L.A....

393
00:25:12,226 --> 00:25:14,660
and a 27 share in both cities.

394
00:25:14,728 --> 00:25:17,925
Last night, Howard Beale went on the air
and yelled " bullshit" for two minutes.

395
00:25:17,998 --> 00:25:22,230
l can tell you tonight's show
will get a 30 share at least.

396
00:25:22,302 --> 00:25:25,533
- l think we've lucked into something.
- For God sakes, Diana!

397
00:25:25,606 --> 00:25:28,803
Are you suggesting we put that lunatic
back on the air yelling " bullshit" ?

398
00:25:28,876 --> 00:25:32,368
Yes, l think we should put Beale back
on the air tonight and keep him on.

399
00:25:32,446 --> 00:25:35,244
Did you see the news this morning?
Did you see the Times?

400
00:25:35,315 --> 00:25:37,943
We got press coverage on this
you couldn't buy for a million dollars.

401
00:25:38,018 --> 00:25:43,957
That show jumped 5 points in one night.
Tonight's show will be at least 15.

402
00:25:44,024 --> 00:25:48,586
We've just increased our audience by
20 or 30 million people in one night!

403
00:25:48,662 --> 00:25:51,426
You won't get something like this dumped
into your lap the rest of your days.

404
00:25:51,498 --> 00:25:55,628
You can't piss it away. Howard said
last night what every American feels.

405
00:25:55,702 --> 00:26:00,765
He's tired of all the bullshit!
He's articulating the popular rage!

406
00:26:00,841 --> 00:26:02,866
l want that show, Frank.

407
00:26:02,943 --> 00:26:05,138
l can turn that show
into the biggest smash on TV.

408
00:26:05,212 --> 00:26:08,204
lt's a news show.
lt's not your department.

409
00:26:08,282 --> 00:26:11,012
l see Howard Beale
as a latter-day prophet...

410
00:26:11,084 --> 00:26:15,180
a messianic figure inveighing
against the hypocrisies of our times!

411
00:26:15,255 --> 00:26:17,815
A strip Savonarola
Monday through Friday...

412
00:26:17,891 --> 00:26:20,257
that will just go through the roof!

413
00:26:20,327 --> 00:26:24,286
And l'm talking about
a six-dollar cost per thousand show.

414
00:26:24,364 --> 00:26:27,424
l'm talking about
130,000 dollar minutes.

415
00:26:27,501 --> 00:26:31,267
Figure out the revenues of a strip show
that sells for $100,000 a minute!

416
00:26:31,338 --> 00:26:35,104
One show like that could pull
this network out of the hole!

417
00:26:35,175 --> 00:26:38,372
lt's being handed to us on a plate.
Let's not blow it.

418
00:26:39,780 --> 00:26:41,680
Yes.

419
00:26:41,748 --> 00:26:43,943
Tell him l'll be a few minutes.

420
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:49,717
- Let me think it over.
- Let's not go to committee on this.

421
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:53,624
lt's 10:20. We want Beale in the studio
by 6:30. We don't want to lose momentum.

422
00:26:53,694 --> 00:26:57,790
For God sakes, we're talking about
putting an irresponsible man...

423
00:26:57,864 --> 00:27:00,355
on national television.

424
00:27:10,110 --> 00:27:12,874
l'd like to talk to Legal Affairs,
Herb Thackery...

425
00:27:12,946 --> 00:27:15,540
and Joe Donnelly
in Standards and Practices.

426
00:27:17,217 --> 00:27:20,414
You know l'll be eyeball to eyeball
with Mr. Ruddy on this.

427
00:27:20,487 --> 00:27:23,684
lf l'm going to the mat with Ruddy,
l want to be sure of my ground.

428
00:27:23,757 --> 00:27:25,987
My ass is going on the line.

429
00:27:29,396 --> 00:27:31,330
l'll get back to you.

430
00:27:35,068 --> 00:27:37,059
l don't believe the top brass...

431
00:27:37,137 --> 00:27:41,198
of a national television network
is sitting around their Caesar salads--

432
00:27:41,275 --> 00:27:43,607
Top brass of a bankrupt
national television network...

433
00:27:43,677 --> 00:27:46,339
with projected losses
of $150 million.

434
00:27:46,413 --> 00:27:47,846
l don't care!

435
00:27:49,283 --> 00:27:53,219
You can't be seriously proposing,
and the rest of us considering...

436
00:27:53,287 --> 00:27:55,812
putting on a pornographic
network news show.

437
00:27:55,889 --> 00:27:58,119
- The FCC would kill us.
- Sit down, Nelson.

438
00:27:58,191 --> 00:28:01,160
The FCC can't do anything
except rap our knuckles.

439
00:28:01,228 --> 00:28:04,391
l don't even want to think about
the litigious possibilities.

440
00:28:04,464 --> 00:28:07,763
-We could be up to our ears in lawsuits.
-The affiliates won't carry it.

441
00:28:07,834 --> 00:28:10,860
The affiliates will kiss your ass
if you can hand them a hit show.

442
00:28:10,937 --> 00:28:13,201
- But popular reaction--
- We don't know the popular reaction.

443
00:28:13,273 --> 00:28:16,470
- That's what we have to find out.
- The New York Times--

444
00:28:16,543 --> 00:28:19,979
The New York Times doesn't advertise
on our network.

445
00:28:21,915 --> 00:28:26,249
All l know is, this violates
every canon of respectable broadcasting.

446
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:29,551
We're not a respectable network.
We're a whorehouse network.

447
00:28:29,623 --> 00:28:31,784
We have to take whatever we can get.

448
00:28:33,226 --> 00:28:35,194
l don't want any part of it.

449
00:28:35,262 --> 00:28:37,730
l don't fancy myself
the president of a whorehouse.

450
00:28:37,798 --> 00:28:40,596
That's commendable of you, Nelson.
Now sit down.

451
00:28:41,735 --> 00:28:43,669
Your indignation
has been duly recorded.

452
00:28:43,737 --> 00:28:45,671
You can always resign tomorrow.

453
00:28:47,941 --> 00:28:51,843
What in substance are we proposing?

454
00:28:51,912 --> 00:28:55,871
Merely to add editorial comment
to our network news show.

455
00:28:55,949 --> 00:28:59,715
Brinkley, Sevareid, Reasoner
all have their comments.

456
00:28:59,786 --> 00:29:01,879
Now Howard Beale will have his.

457
00:29:01,955 --> 00:29:06,016
l think we ought to give it a shot,
see what happens tonight. Telephone.

458
00:29:06,093 --> 00:29:09,551
l don't want to be the messenger
who has to tell Schumacher about this.

459
00:29:09,629 --> 00:29:13,395
He doesn't work at this network anymore.
Mr. Ruddy fired him last night.

460
00:29:13,467 --> 00:29:16,436
Bob McDonough is running
the News Division now.

461
00:29:17,838 --> 00:29:19,829
Bob McDonough in News, please.

462
00:29:21,341 --> 00:29:23,468
l don't know.

463
00:29:23,543 --> 00:29:26,011
l may teach or write a book--

464
00:29:26,079 --> 00:29:30,175
whatever the hell one does when one
approaches the autumn of one's years.

465
00:29:32,986 --> 00:29:34,920
