Was l ever that young?

467
00:29:38,258 --> 00:29:40,692
No, Howard brought in a picture
of Ed Murrow...

468
00:29:40,761 --> 00:29:43,252
and the CBS gang
when we were there.

469
00:29:43,330 --> 00:29:44,854
You wouldn't believe it!

470
00:29:44,931 --> 00:29:47,058
Walter Cronkite, Harry Reasoner...

471
00:29:47,134 --> 00:29:49,159
Hollenbeck, Bob Trout.

472
00:29:49,236 --> 00:29:51,170
ls that you?

473
00:29:52,339 --> 00:29:56,105
Yeah. Okay, Dick,
we'll be in touch.

474
00:29:56,176 --> 00:30:00,579
Remember this kid you sent to interview
Cleveland Amory on vivisection?

475
00:30:04,317 --> 00:30:06,547
What's so funny?

476
00:30:09,156 --> 00:30:12,683
l jump out of bed in my pajamas,
l grab my raincoat, l run downstairs.

477
00:30:12,759 --> 00:30:15,387
l run out to the street
and hail a cab.

478
00:30:15,462 --> 00:30:20,490
l yell at the driver, " Take me to the
middle of the George Washington Bridge."

479
00:30:22,602 --> 00:30:26,299
And the driver says,
"Don't do it, buddy. Don't do it!

480
00:30:26,373 --> 00:30:28,864
You're young. You've got
your whole life ahead of you."

481
00:30:29,843 --> 00:30:32,175
Wait a minute.

482
00:30:32,245 --> 00:30:36,773
lf you think that's funny,
wait till you hear this.

483
00:30:36,850 --> 00:30:38,784
l've come from Hackett's office.

484
00:30:38,852 --> 00:30:41,616
He wants to put Howard
back on the air tonight.

485
00:30:41,688 --> 00:30:44,782
Apparently the ratings went up
five points last night...

486
00:30:44,858 --> 00:30:48,123
and he wants Howard to go back on
and do his " angry man" thing.

487
00:30:48,195 --> 00:30:50,288
What are you talking about?

488
00:30:50,363 --> 00:30:53,423
They want Howard to go back on
and yell " bullshit."

489
00:30:56,036 --> 00:30:57,970
They want Howard to go on...

490
00:30:58,038 --> 00:31:00,029
spontaneously letting out
his anger.

491
00:31:00,106 --> 00:31:03,075
A latter-day prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times.

492
00:31:03,143 --> 00:31:05,373
That sounds pretty good!

493
00:31:06,279 --> 00:31:07,712
Who's " they" ?

494
00:31:07,781 --> 00:31:10,443
Hackett. Chaney was there.

495
00:31:10,517 --> 00:31:13,645
The Legal Affairs guy.
Oh, and that girl from programming.

496
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:16,154
Christensen?
What's she got to do with this?

497
00:31:16,223 --> 00:31:18,987
- Are you kidding?
- l'm not kidding.

498
00:31:19,059 --> 00:31:22,790
l said, " We're running
a news department here, not a circus.

499
00:31:22,863 --> 00:31:25,423
And Howard Beale's
not a bearded lady.

500
00:31:25,499 --> 00:31:28,127
lf you think l'll go along with
this bastardization of the news...

501
00:31:28,201 --> 00:31:31,637
you can have my resignation
along with Max Schumacher's.

502
00:31:31,705 --> 00:31:37,541
- l'm speaking for Howard Beale and--"
- That's my job you're turning down.

503
00:31:37,611 --> 00:31:40,444
l'd go nuts
without some kind of work.

504
00:31:40,514 --> 00:31:44,541
What's wrong with being an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

505
00:31:44,618 --> 00:31:46,313
What do you think, Max?

506
00:31:46,386 --> 00:31:50,618
Do you want to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

507
00:31:50,690 --> 00:31:55,184
Yeah, l'd like to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times.

508
00:31:56,463 --> 00:31:58,454
Then grab it!

509
00:32:04,938 --> 00:32:06,872
- Afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.
- Afternoon.

510
00:32:06,940 --> 00:32:08,874
Good afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.

511
00:32:12,012 --> 00:32:14,344
- He's waiting for you.
- Thank you.

512
00:32:20,654 --> 00:32:24,021
Nelson Chaney tells me Beale
may actually go on the air this evening.

513
00:32:25,825 --> 00:32:28,157
As far as l know,
Howard's going to do it.

514
00:32:30,764 --> 00:32:33,494
- Are you gonna sit still for this?
- Yes.

515
00:32:33,567 --> 00:32:36,297
l think Hackett's overstepped himself.

516
00:32:36,369 --> 00:32:38,929
There's some kind of
corporate maneuvering going on.

517
00:32:39,005 --> 00:32:41,530
Hackett is clearly forcing
a confrontation.

518
00:32:41,608 --> 00:32:43,803
That would account for his behavior
at the stockholders' meeting.

519
00:32:43,877 --> 00:32:48,473
However, l think he's making a serious
mistake with this Beale business.

520
00:32:48,548 --> 00:32:51,676
l suspect CCA will be upset...

521
00:32:51,751 --> 00:32:53,719
at Hackett's presumptuousness.

522
00:32:53,787 --> 00:32:55,948
Certainly Mr. Jensen will.

523
00:32:56,022 --> 00:32:59,583
So l'm going to let Hackett
have his head for a while.

524
00:32:59,659 --> 00:33:02,321
He just might lose it
over this Beale business.

525
00:33:06,533 --> 00:33:09,331
l'd like you to reconsider
your resignation.

526
00:33:09,402 --> 00:33:11,893
l assume Hackett
wouldn't take such steps...

527
00:33:11,972 --> 00:33:14,270
without some support
on the CCA board.

528
00:33:14,341 --> 00:33:17,208
l'll have to go directly to Mr. Jensen.

529
00:33:17,277 --> 00:33:20,508
When that happens, l'm going to need
every friend l've got...

530
00:33:20,580 --> 00:33:24,277
and l don't want Hackett's people
in all the divisional positions.

531
00:33:24,351 --> 00:33:26,546
So l'd like you to stay on.

532
00:33:31,091 --> 00:33:32,524
Of course.

533
00:33:34,227 --> 00:33:36,957
Thank you, Max.

534
00:33:37,030 --> 00:33:39,498
This has been
the " UBS Evening News" ...

535
00:33:39,566 --> 00:33:42,000
with Howard Beale.

536
00:33:42,068 --> 00:33:44,696
The initial response to the new
"Howard Beale Show" ...

537
00:33:44,771 --> 00:33:46,830
was not auspicatory.

538
00:33:46,906 --> 00:33:48,931
The press was,
without exception, hostile...

539
00:33:49,009 --> 00:33:51,204
and industry reaction negative.

540
00:33:51,277 --> 00:33:53,609
The ratings for the Thursday
and Friday shows...

541
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:56,205
were both 14,
but Monday's rating dropped a point...

542
00:33:56,282 --> 00:33:59,547
clearly suggesting the novelty
was wearing off.

543
00:34:01,354 --> 00:34:03,549
Did you know there are
a number of psychics...

544
00:34:03,623 --> 00:34:06,558
working as licensed brokers
on Wall Street?

545
00:34:06,626 --> 00:34:09,060
Some counsel their clients
by use of tarot cards.

546
00:34:09,129 --> 00:34:12,860
They're all pretty successful,
even in a bear market and selling short.

547
00:34:12,932 --> 00:34:16,527
l met one of them last week
and thought of doing a show around her.

548
00:34:16,603 --> 00:34:19,231
"The Wayward Witch of Wall Street."
Something like that.

549
00:34:19,305 --> 00:34:21,830
But if her tips were any good,
she could wreck the market.

550
00:34:21,908 --> 00:34:27,437
l called her this morning and asked her
how she was on predicting the future.

551
00:34:27,514 --> 00:34:30,210
She said she was
occasionally prescient.

552
00:34:30,283 --> 00:34:34,913
"For example," she said,
"l just had a vision of you...

553
00:34:34,988 --> 00:34:37,980
sitting in an office
with a craggy, middle-aged man...

554
00:34:38,058 --> 00:34:41,494
with whom you are
or will be emotionally involved."

555
00:34:41,561 --> 00:34:43,153
And here l am.

556
00:34:45,632 --> 00:34:48,192
She does all this with tarot cards?

557
00:34:48,268 --> 00:34:51,135
This one operates
on parapsychology.

558
00:34:51,204 --> 00:34:55,504
She has trance-like episodes
and feels things in her energy field.

559
00:34:56,476 --> 00:35:00,173
- This lady could be very useful to you.
- ln what way?

560
00:35:00,246 --> 00:35:02,840
You put on a news show.

561
00:35:02,916 --> 00:35:06,147
And here's somebody who can predict
tomorrow's news for you.

562
00:35:06,219 --> 00:35:08,551
Her name, aptly enough, is Sibyl.

563
00:35:08,621 --> 00:35:10,555
Sibyl the Soothsayer.

564
00:35:10,623 --> 00:35:13,217
You could give her
two minutes of trance...

565
00:35:13,293 --> 00:35:15,887
at the end of the " Howard Beale Show,"
say once a week, Friday...

566
00:35:15,962 --> 00:35:18,396
which is suggestively occult,
and she could oraculate.

567
00:35:19,632 --> 00:35:22,567
Then next week everyone tunes in to see
how good her predictions were.

568
00:35:23,703 --> 00:35:25,728
Maybe she could do the weather.

569
00:35:28,041 --> 00:35:31,010
Your " Network News Show" will need help
if it's going to hold.

570
00:35:31,077 --> 00:35:33,568
Beale doesn't do the " angry man" thing
well at all.

571
00:35:33,646 --> 00:35:35,671
He's too kvetchy.
He's being irascible.

572
00:35:35,749 --> 00:35:38,912
We want a prophet, not a curmudgeon.
He should do more apocalyptic doom.

573
00:35:38,985 --> 00:35:42,819
l think you should have some writers
write some jeremiads for him.

574
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:46,454
l see you don't fancy my suggestions.

575
00:35:48,661 --> 00:35:50,492
You're not serious?

576
00:35:50,563 --> 00:35:52,292
l'm serious.

577
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:56,325
The fact is, l could make
your Beale show...

578
00:35:56,402 --> 00:36:00,361
the highest-rated news show in TV
if you'd let me have a crack at it.

579
00:36:01,341 --> 00:36:03,571
What do you mean,
"have a crack at it" ?

580
00:36:03,643 --> 00:36:05,508
l'd like to program it for you.

581
00:36:05,578 --> 00:36:07,170
Develop it.

582
00:36:07,247 --> 00:36:11,946
l wouldn't interfere with
the news itself, but TV is show biz...

583
00:36:12,018 --> 00:36:15,954
and even the news has to have
a little showmanship.

584
00:36:16,022 --> 00:36:18,286
My God, you are serious.

585
00:36:18,358 --> 00:36:22,522
l watched your six o'clock news today.
lt's straight tabloid.

586
00:36:22,595 --> 00:36:26,122
You had a minute and a half of that lady
riding naked in Central Park...

587
00:36:26,199 --> 00:36:29,293
but you had less than a minute
of hard national and international news.

588
00:36:29,369 --> 00:36:32,065
lt was all sex, scandal,
brutal crime, sports...

589
00:36:32,138 --> 00:36:35,471
children with incurable diseases
and lost puppies.

590
00:36:35,542 --> 00:36:38,943
So l won't listen to protestations
of high standards of journalism...

591
00:36:39,012 --> 00:36:41,879
when you're on the streets, soliciting
audiences like the rest of us.

592
00:36:41,948 --> 00:36:45,975
All l'm saying is, if you're going
to hustle, at least do it right.

593
00:36:46,052 --> 00:36:49,146
l'm going to bring this up at tomorrow's
meeting, but l don't like hassles.

594
00:36:49,222 --> 00:36:52,589
l was hoping we could work this out
between us. That's why l'm here.

595
00:36:54,127 --> 00:36:57,494
And l was hoping you were looking for
an emotional involvement...

596
00:36:57,564 --> 00:36:59,759
with a craggy, middle-aged man.

597
00:37:01,301 --> 00:37:03,326
l wouldn't rule that out entirely.

598
00:37:06,739 --> 00:37:09,071
All right, Diana...

599
00:37:09,142 --> 00:37:12,873
bring up all your ideas at the meeting,
because if you don't, l will.

600
00:37:14,380 --> 00:37:16,848
l think Howard's making
a goddamn fool of himself...

601
00:37:16,916 --> 00:37:21,046
and so does everybody that Howard
and l know in this industry.

602
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:23,486
lt was a fluke.
Didn't work.

603
00:37:24,757 --> 00:37:27,851
So tomorrow, Howard goes back
to the old format...

604
00:37:27,927 --> 00:37:31,795
and all of this gutter depravity
comes to an end.

605
00:37:43,476 --> 00:37:45,341
l don't get it.

606
00:37:46,813 --> 00:37:49,805
You hung around until 7:30
and then came down here...

607
00:37:49,883 --> 00:37:52,818
just to pitch a couple
of loony show-biz ideas...

608
00:37:52,886 --> 00:37:56,788
when you knew goddamn well
l'd laugh you right out of the office.

609
00:37:56,856 --> 00:37:59,256
l don't get it.

610
00:37:59,325 --> 00:38:02,158
What's your scam in this?

611
00:38:02,228 --> 00:38:07,632
My visit here tonight was a gesture made
out of your stature in the industry...

612
00:38:08,935 --> 00:38:11,631
and because l personally admired you
since l was a kid...

613
00:38:11,704 --> 00:38:14,229
majoring in speech
at the University of Missouri.

614
00:38:15,508 --> 00:38:19,274
Sooner or later, with or without you,
l'm going to take over your news show.

615
00:38:19,345 --> 00:38:21,870
l figured l might as well start tonight.

616
00:38:23,149 --> 00:38:25,845
l think l once gave a lecture...

617
00:38:25,919 --> 00:38:29,184
at the University of Missouri.

618
00:38:29,255 --> 00:38:33,919
l was in the audience. l had
a schoolgirl crush on you for months.

619
00:38:35,561 --> 00:38:38,928
lf we could get back for a moment
to that gypsy who predicted...

620
00:38:38,998 --> 00:38:43,230
all that about emotional involvements
and middle-aged men...

621
00:38:44,437 --> 00:38:46,871
what are you doing
for dinner tonight?

622
00:38:56,182 --> 00:38:58,878
l can't make it tonight.
Call me tomorrow.

623
00:39:01,387 --> 00:39:04,550
- Do you have a favorite restaurant?
- l eat anything.

624
00:39:05,925 --> 00:39:08,120
l get a feeling l'm being made.

625
00:39:08,194 --> 00:39:09,627
You are.

626
00:39:10,797 --> 00:39:13,960
l've got to warn you.
l don't do anything on my first date.

627
00:39:14,033 --> 00:39:15,466
We'll see.

628
00:39:21,474 --> 00:39:23,738
Schmuck, what are you getting into?

629
00:39:45,198 --> 00:39:49,259
l was married for four years
and pretended to be happy.

630
00:39:49,335 --> 00:39:51,963
l had six years of analysis
and pretended to be sane.

631
00:39:53,773 --> 00:39:56,435
My husband ran off
with his boyfriend...

632
00:39:56,509 --> 00:40:01,105
and l had an affair with my analyst who
told me l was the worst lay he ever had.

633
00:40:02,382 --> 00:40:05,283
l can't tell you how many men
have told me what a lousy lay l am.

634
00:40:06,152 --> 00:40:08,586
l apparently have
a masculine temperament.

635
00:40:08,654 --> 00:40:12,522
l arouse quickly,
consummate prematurely...

636
00:40:12,592 --> 00:40:15,652
and l can't wait to get my clothes
back on and get out of that bedroom.

637
00:40:16,896 --> 00:40:20,832
l seem to be inept at everything
except my work.

638
00:40:21,734 --> 00:40:23,964
l'm good at my work.

639
00:40:24,037 --> 00:40:26,597
So l confine myself to that.

640
00:40:26,672 --> 00:40:30,130
All l want out of life
is a 30 share and a 20 rating.

641
00:40:31,711 --> 00:40:33,838
You're married, surely?

642
00:40:35,415 --> 00:40:36,848
Twenty-five years.

643
00:40:37,917 --> 00:40:41,182
l have a married daughter in Seattle
who's six months pregnant...

644
00:40:41,254 --> 00:40:46,419
and a younger girl who's starting
at Northwestern in January.

645
00:40:49,295 --> 00:40:51,195
Well, Max, here we are.

646
00:40:53,266 --> 00:40:56,030
Middle-aged man reaffirming
his middle-aged manhood...

647
00:40:56,102 --> 00:40:59,094
and a terrified young woman
with a father complex.

648
00:40:59,172 --> 00:41:01,663
What sort of script
can we make out of this?

649
00:41:03,743 --> 00:41:08,146
Corridor gossip says that you're
Frank Hackett's backstage girl.

650
00:41:09,182 --> 00:41:10,615
l'm not.

651
00:41:12,285 --> 00:41:15,652
Frank's a corporation man,
body and soul.

652
00:41:15,721 --> 00:41:17,712
He has no loves, lusts
or allegiances...

653
00:41:17,790 --> 00:41:21,248
that are not consummately directed
toward becoming a CCA board member.

654
00:41:21,327 --> 00:41:24,160
Why should he bother with me?
l'm not even a stockholder.

655
00:41:26,032 --> 00:41:30,298
What about your loves,
lusts and allegiances?

656
00:41:30,369 --> 00:41:32,530
ls your wife in town?

657
00:41:32,605 --> 00:41:34,038
Yes.

658
00:41:35,308 --> 00:41:37,776
Then we better go to my place.

659
00:41:39,178 --> 00:41:42,113
l can't hear you.
You'll have to talk a little louder.

660
00:41:48,855 --> 00:41:51,881
Yes, l hear you.

661
00:41:55,461 --> 00:41:56,894
Yes.

662
00:41:59,699 --> 00:42:01,132
Yes.

663
00:42:07,073 --> 00:42:08,540
Why me?

664
00:42:10,476 --> 00:42:12,706
l said, " Why me?"

665
00:42:33,065 --> 00:42:35,033
Howard in his office?

666
00:42:36,169 --> 00:42:41,232
l'm killing this whole screwball
"angry prophet" thing.

667
00:42:41,307 --> 00:42:43,537
Tonight we go back to straight news.

668
00:42:50,416 --> 00:42:53,977
Yeah? Max, l'm telling you he's fine.

669
00:42:54,053 --> 00:42:57,113
He's been sharp all day.
He's been as funny as hell.

670
00:42:57,190 --> 00:42:59,420
Had everybody cracking up
at the rundown meeting.

671
00:42:59,492 --> 00:43:01,483
l told him!

672
00:43:02,295 --> 00:43:03,728
Cue VTA.

673
00:43:04,497 --> 00:43:05,930
Ready two.

674
00:43:08,234 --> 00:43:11,499
- Cue announcer.
- The " UBS Evening News" ...

675
00:43:11,571 --> 00:43:13,596
with Howard Beale.

676
00:43:14,607 --> 00:43:18,441
Last night l was awakened
from a fitful sleep...

677
00:43:18,511 --> 00:43:21,173
shortly after 2:00 in the morning...

678
00:43:21,247 --> 00:43:24,307
by a shrill, sibilant,
faceless voice.

679
00:43:24,383 --> 00:43:28,012
l couldn't make it out at first
in the dark bedroom.

680
00:43:29,555 --> 00:43:32,183
l said, " l'm sorry.
You'll have to talk a little louder."

681
00:43:32,258 --> 00:43:35,955
- What do you want me to do?
- Nothing.

682
00:43:36,028 --> 00:43:39,327
The voice said to me,
"l want you to tell the truth.

683
00:43:39,398 --> 00:43:42,265
Not easy to do, because the people
don't want to know the truth."

684
00:43:42,335 --> 00:43:45,065
l said, " You're kidding?

685
00:43:45,137 --> 00:43:47,071
What should l know about the truth?"

686
00:43:47,139 --> 00:43:51,701
But the voice said to me,
"Don't worry about the truth."

687
00:43:51,777 --> 00:43:53,745
l will put the words in your mouth."

688
00:43:54,814 --> 00:43:56,748
l said,
"ls this the burning bush?

689
00:43:56,816 --> 00:43:58,249
l'm not Moses."

690
00:43:58,317 --> 00:44:01,582
The voice said, " l'm not God.
What has that got to do with it?"

691
00:44:01,654 --> 00:44:06,023
The voice said, " We're not talking
about eternal, absolute truth.

692
00:44:06,092 --> 00:44:08,822
We're talking about impermanent,
transient, human truth!

693
00:44:08,894 --> 00:44:11,795
l don't expect people
to be capable of truth...

694
00:44:11,864 --> 00:44:14,389
but at least you're capable
of self-preservation."

695
00:44:15,501 --> 00:44:19,232
l said, " Why me?"

696
00:44:19,305 --> 00:44:22,035
The voice said, " Because you're
on television, dummy."

697
00:44:22,108 --> 00:44:24,338
Beautiful.

698
00:44:24,410 --> 00:44:27,538
"Forty million Americans listen to you,
and after the show, maybe 50 million.

699
00:44:27,613 --> 00:44:31,845
l'm not asking you to walk the land
in sackcloth preaching the Armageddon.

700
00:44:31,917 --> 00:44:33,350
You're on TV."

